        "text": "The pitcher’s father had crossed half the infield by then. He was a heavy man and not built for sprinting. He ran with one hand pressed against his side because of an old shingles flare he had been ignoring for two weeks, and the running was making it sing, and he was running anyway. He had loved his son, on and off, for ten years, and he had said it three times. Saturday was for fixing that. Saturday had a beer in it for after, and the apology he had been working out in the truck on the way over was about a fishing trip that had not happened in 2009. He was going to say it on the drive home. He was going to say it now."
